word_mean_info__list.difference: 可与melt换用，但侧重指在高温下使两种或两种以上金属的熔合，也可作引申用。
多指固体溶于溶剂的过程。
最常用词，指任何固体的熔化过程，常引申作“消散、淡化或消失”解。

bilingual.source: Use a solvent to dissolve the paint.

bilingual.target: 柠檬汁可以帮助溶解脂肪。

bilingual.source: The tablet will dissolve in your mouth.
bilingual.target: 这片药会在你嘴里溶解。
这些咖啡颗粒溶解得很快。
聚维酮可以帮助药物更好地溶解。

bilingual.source: Sugar will quickly dissolve in hot water.
bilingual.target: 糖在热水中很快就溶解了。

bilingual.source: They used medication to dissolve the thrombus.
bilingual.target: 他们使用药物来溶解血栓。
亲水分子在水中容易溶解。

bilingual.source: You can use warm water to dissolve these powders.
bilingual.target: 你可以用温水溶解这些粉末。

bilingual.source: Nonpolar molecules do not dissolve well in water.
bilingual.target: 非极性分子在水中不易溶解。

list.abstract: Dissolve，英语单词，动词、名词，作动词时译为“使溶解；使分解；使液化；溶解；解散；消失”，作名词时译为“叠化画面；画面的溶暗”。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh. What's wrong? I drew my own bath, but I did it wrong. The water's tepid. The salt didn't dissolve and is now lodged places.
yingyinNormal.zh: 怎么了？我自己放洗澡水，但我没有弄对水温温的，浴盐无法溶解，现在它们结块了。

yingyinNormal.en: But even if we were to make a deal tonight, my concern is that it would dissolve very quickly.
yingyinNormal.zh: 但即使我们今晚就达成协议，我担心律所也会很快分崩离析。

yingyinNormal.en: The time has come to dissolve the IMF. Mr. Chairman. And transfer the salvageable assets to the CIA.
yingyinNormal.zh: 是时候解散碟中谍小组了。主席先生。然后把其资源和人员调拨给中情局。

yingyinNormal.en: As I accept all of your letters of resignation and dissolve my old cabinet, I wanna welcome each and every one of you to my new cabinet.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我正式接受各位的辞呈并解散我的旧内阁，然后我想欢迎在座的各位加入我的新内阁。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation: 多指固体溶于溶剂的过程。
可与 melt 换用, 但侧重指在高温下使两种或两种以上金属的熔合, 也可作引申用。
最常用词, 指任何固体的熔化过程, 常引申作"消散、淡化或消失"解。
